{"parse":{"title":"Rowett Research Institute","pageid":4566207,"revid":844672862,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Rowett_004.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Rowett_004.jpg/220px-Rowett_004.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"202\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Rowett_004.jpg/330px-Rowett_004.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Rowett_004.jpg/440px-Rowett_004.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4912\" data-file-height=\"4520\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Rowett_004.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Exterior of the new building on the Foresterhill Health Campus</div></div></div>\n<table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Refimprove\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"39\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/75px-Question_book-new.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/100px-Question_book-new.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"399\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>needs additional citations for <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">verification</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Rowett_Research_Institute&amp;action=edit\">improve this article</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing_with_Wiki_Markup/1\" title=\"Help:Introduction to referencing with Wiki Markup/1\">adding citations to reliable sources</a>. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed.</span>  <small><i>(September 2015)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Rowett_Institute_-_geograph.org.uk_-_23214.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Rowett_Institute_-_geograph.org.uk_-_23214.jpg/220px-Rowett_Institute_-_geograph.org.uk_-_23214.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"293\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Rowett_Institute_-_geograph.org.uk_-_23214.jpg/330px-Rowett_Institute_-_geograph.org.uk_-_23214.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Rowett_Institute_-_geograph.org.uk_-_23214.jpg/440px-Rowett_Institute_-_geograph.org.uk_-_23214.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"480\" data-file-height=\"640\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Rowett_Institute_-_geograph.org.uk_-_23214.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Reid Library at the old Bucksburn site</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Rowett Institute for Nutrition and Health</b> is a research centre for studies into <a href=\"/wiki/Food_science\" title=\"Food science\">food</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Nutrition\" title=\"Nutrition\">nutrition</a>, located in <a href=\"/wiki/Aberdeen\" title=\"Aberdeen\">Aberdeen</a>, Scotland.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Notable_alumni\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notable alumni</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Notable_Staff\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notable Staff</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rowett_Research_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The institute was founded in 1913 when the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Aberdeen\" title=\"University of Aberdeen\">University of Aberdeen</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/Scottish_Agricultural_College\" title=\"Scottish Agricultural College\">North of Scotland College of Agriculture</a> agreed that an \"Institute for Research into Animal Nutrition\" should be established in Scotland. The first director was <a href=\"/wiki/John_Boyd_Orr\" title=\"John Boyd Orr\">John Boyd Orr</a>, later to become <b>Lord Boyd Orr</b>, who moved from <a href=\"/wiki/Glasgow\" title=\"Glasgow\">Glasgow</a> to \"the wilds of Aberdeenshire\" in 1914. Orr drew up some plans for a nutrition research institute. Orr also donated \u00a35000 for the building of a granite <a href=\"/wiki/Laboratory\" title=\"Laboratory\">laboratory</a> building at Craibstone, not far from the Bucksburn site of the Rowett.\n</p><p>At the breakout of the <a href=\"/wiki/Great_War\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Great War\">Great War</a>, Orr left the Institute, but returned in 1919 with a staff of four to begin work in the new laboratory. Orr continued to push for a new research institute and finally the <a href=\"/wiki/Her_Majesty%27s_Government\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Her Majesty&#39;s Government\">Government</a> agreed to pay half the costs but stipulated that the other half was to be found from other sources. The extra money was donated by Dr <a href=\"/wiki/John_Quiller_Rowett\" title=\"John Quiller Rowett\">John Quiller Rowett</a>, a <a href=\"/wiki/Businessman\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Businessman\">businessman</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Board_of_directors\" title=\"Board of directors\">director</a> of a wine and spirits merchants in London. \n</p><p>Rowett's donation allowed the purchase of  41 <a href=\"/wiki/Acre\" title=\"Acre\">acres</a> of land for the Institute to be built on. Rowett also contributed \u00a310,000 towards the cost of the buildings. The money was donated with one very important stipulation from Rowett \u2014 \"if any work done at the Institute on animal nutrition were found to have a bearing on human nutrition, the Institute would be allowed to follow up this work.\" The Institute was formally opened in 1922 by <a href=\"/wiki/Mary_of_Teck\" title=\"Mary of Teck\">Queen Mary</a>.\n</p><p>On 1 July 2008 the Institute merged with the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Aberdeen\" title=\"University of Aberdeen\">University of Aberdeen</a> to become the Rowett Institute of Nutrition and Health, College of Life Sciences and Medicine.\n</p><p>In March 2016 the Rowett Institute relocated to a purpose-built building at the University's Medical School campus at Foresterhill, Aberdeen.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notable_alumni\">Notable alumni</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rowett_Research_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Notable alumni\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Ainsley_Iggo\" title=\"Ainsley Iggo\">Ainsley Iggo</a>, known for demonstrating electrical recording from individual C fibres in the human body. President of the <a href=\"/wiki/International_Association_for_the_Study_of_Pain\" title=\"International Association for the Study of Pain\">International Association for the Study of Pain</a> (IASP) (1981-84).</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Joseph_Heald\" title=\"Peter Joseph Heald\">Peter Joseph Heald</a>, known for his research on reproductive biochemistry.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Winifred_Margaret_Deans\" title=\"Winifred Margaret Deans\">Winifred Margaret Dean</a>, prolific translator of German scientific texts into English.</li></ul>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Strathcona_House_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1563336.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Strathcona_House_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1563336.jpg/220px-Strathcona_House_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1563336.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"146\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Strathcona_House_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1563336.jpg/330px-Strathcona_House_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1563336.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Strathcona_House_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1563336.jpg/440px-Strathcona_House_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1563336.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"640\" data-file-height=\"426\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Strathcona_House_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1563336.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Strathcona House</div></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notable_Staff\">Notable Staff</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rowett_Research_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notable Staff\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/A._T._Phillipson\" title=\"A. T. Phillipson\">A. T. Phillipson</a> Head of Physiology 1947 to 1963 and Depute Director from 1952.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/John_Boyd_Orr\" title=\"John Boyd Orr\">John Boyd Orr</a>, Director from 1914-1945, recipient of A <a href=\"/wiki/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel Peace Prize</a> for his research into nutrition and work as first Director-General of the <a href=\"/wiki/Food_and_Agriculture_Organization\" title=\"Food and Agriculture Organization\">United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/%C3%81rp%C3%A1d_Pusztai\" title=\"\u00c1rp\u00e1d Pusztai\">\u00c1rp\u00e1d Pusztai</a>, researcher at the Institute from 1963 to 1999, noted expert in plant pectins and known for starting the <a href=\"/wiki/Pusztai_affair\" title=\"Pusztai affair\">Pusztai Affair</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Asim_Duttaroy\" title=\"Asim Duttaroy\">Asim K. Duttaroy</a>, Professor at the Institute from 1990 to 2001, currently Professor of clinical nutrition at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Oslo\" title=\"University of Oslo\">University of Oslo</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Richard_Laurence_Millington_Synge\" title=\"Richard Laurence Millington Synge\">Richard Laurence Millington Synge</a>, researcher at the Institute from 1948 to 1967, recipient of a <a href=\"/wiki/Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Chemistry\">Nobel Prize in Chemistry</a> for the invention of partition chromatography.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Kenneth_Blaxter_(animal_nutritionist)\" title=\"Kenneth Blaxter (animal nutritionist)\">Kenneth Blaxter</a>, Director from 1965 until 1982.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Joseph_Fairweather_Lamb\" title=\"Joseph Fairweather Lamb\">Joseph Fairweather Lamb</a>, Director from 1998-2003.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rowett_Research_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.abdn.ac.uk/rowett/index.php\">Rowett Institute of Nutrition and Health</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.abdn.ac.uk/rowett-centenary/index.php\">Celebrating 100 years of the Rowett</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1252\nCached time: 20180911184129\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.056 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.090 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 276/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 5066/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 250/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 3/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.017/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 986 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   63.777      1 -total\n 51.74%   32.998      1 Template:Refimprove\n 46.16%   29.437      1 Template:Ambox\n 41.23%   26.296      1 Template:Use_dmy_dates\n 23.57%   15.032      2 Template:DMCA\n 17.79%   11.347      2 Template:Dated_maintenance_category\n 11.37%    7.251      2 Template:FULLROOTPAGENAME\n  8.43%    5.376      2 Template:Ns_has_subpages\n  6.83%    4.355      1 Template:Use_British_English\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:4566207-0!canonical and timestamp 20180911184129 and revision id 844672862\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[{"lang":"ar","url":"ht